<p>Fort Lauderdale residents have access to several valuable incentives that make solar and HVAC upgrades more affordable. The federal Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit for solar installations through 2032, reducing to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. Florida offers additional benefits including no state income tax on solar equipment and a property tax exemption for the added home value from solar installations. This means a \$20,000 solar system won't increase your property taxes, despite potentially adding \$15,000+ to your home's value.</p>

<p>FPL participates in various rebate programs throughout the year, including rebates for high-efficiency HVAC systems, smart thermostats, and energy-efficient home improvements. The utility's Energy Manager program provides free energy audits and personalized recommendations for reducing consumption. Additionally, Florida's net metering law requires utilities to credit customers for excess solar energy at retail rates, maximizing the financial benefits of solar installations. Local financing options, including PACE (Property Assessed Clean Energy) programs, allow homeowners to finance solar and HVAC improvements with no upfront costs, paying through property tax assessments over 15-20 years.</p>

